Ι have not been able to find any confirmation of the list of religious here given, as the Monosticon has a hiatus in the list of abbots for each monastery concerned. In connexion with the introduction of a new foreign order at Sion so soon after the confiscation of the lands of alien cells, it is interesting that the Cluniac priory of S. Saviour of Bermondsey had only in 1399 been made an independent abbey.
